@startuml sequence_skill_install
!theme plain

title Skill Installation and Agent Discovery Flow

actor Developer
participant "create-code-cli" as CLI
participant "InstallCommand" as Cmd
participant "File System" as FS
actor "AI Agent" as Agent
participant "CodeGenerator\nFramework" as CG

== Installation ==

Developer -> CLI: create-code-cli install -o /project
CLI -> Cmd: HandleAsync(outputDirectory)
Cmd -> Cmd: Read SkillContent constant
Cmd -> FS: Directory.CreateDirectory(\n.claude/skills/code-generator/)
Cmd -> FS: File.WriteAllTextAsync(\nSKILL.md, SkillContent)
FS --> Cmd: Written
Cmd --> Developer: "Installed Claude skill: {path}"

== Agent Discovery ==

Developer -> Agent: "Generate a Flask REST API\nwith User model"
Agent -> FS: Read .claude/skills/\ncode-generator/SKILL.md
FS --> Agent: Skill documentation\n(all 8 modules)

Agent -> Agent: Parse Flask section:\nControllerModel, ModelModel,\nRepositoryModel, ServiceModel,\nSchemaModel, AppFactoryModel

Agent -> Agent: Build generation plan:\n1. Register services\n2. Create models\n3. Call GenerateAsync

Agent -> CG: services.AddFlaskServices()
Agent -> CG: new ControllerModel("User")
Agent -> CG: new ModelModel("User")
Agent -> CG: artifactGenerator.GenerateAsync(model)
CG --> Agent: Generated Flask files

Agent --> Developer: Flask API with User model

@enduml
